The paper focuses on developing an adaptive guidance system for equipment operators, which involves modeling user behavior and skill levels. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. Additionally, the study involves capturing and analyzing visual data using a head-mounted camera and gaze tracker, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The study also involves modeling user behavior using machine learning techniques, which suggests that the paper may belong to the Robotics (cs.RO), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
